Worry not, to everyone wondering/still confused. This was an excellently good ending. If any of you recall the "Love Me" work, Manaka was asking Yuika on how she can let herself be spoiled by her spouse, Kenjirou. Yuika (who was yet to be revealed at that time) gave her advice on said matter. Turns out, she herself was facing that same problem of not knowing what it feels like to be spoiled. And in the last page (this work), we see her confessing the she was just talking big (lying by giving superficial advice) at that time. Now that she accepts Hayato (became a couple in the most classic tsundere fashion), Yuika wants to practice more with her little sister (since she still feels too embarrassed to be spoiled by Hayato). My apologies for the long explanation lads, just wanted to help out. Thank you for reading and have a wonderful day.
